The paper deals with iterative thresholding algorithms for sparse recovery and compressive sensing, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP) communities. The proposed method is based on applying the Stein unbiased risk estimate (SURE), which is a statistical technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper mentions connections between the proposed method and LASSO, which is a popular method in statistics and optimization (cs.SI).
